<br>
Getting your epic, any epic is not just a matter of going through the motions and doing some things.  Its a matter of associating with people making friends and building skills.  Not trade skills but actually...  Leadership skills  &lt;omg&gt;  what was verant thinking for making people want to try and do something like that for.  (that was sarcasm)<br>
<br>
Seriously, epic encounters are supposed to be something where the interested person rallies people (friends they have made or guildi's that will help) to come to their aid.  There's really a lot of things going on thats just basically saying heck with it... everyone has to help me regardless of my attitude.  Regardless of the associations I make in the game, and the friendships I seek, You will help me get what I want because my name is on a list.<br>
<br>
I think a list is a good idea, I just do not like the way it is being done.  I see a great level of frustration from people who have all the parts of the cleric epic done, and then anger when one of the listed folks gets the ragefire and then runs to chardock to get help for the king.  <br>
<br>
I say this as I think back to the weeks that I spent camping the ragefire spawn before the change, for several guild clerics.  Having to help form Multiple nagafen raids as there was a huge amount of patches  (grrrr).  Thing is, those people that finished the epic had formed friendships and alliances that allowed for them to succesfully gather support for an epic raid. <br>
<br>
 I rather feel like this list takes that effort out of the clerics hands and tries to force those people with the ability to lead, and kill ragefire to do so.  Regardless of who they are doing it for just so its done and over with while the real person responsible for getting their cleric has but to sit in a zone and wait for their reward for time waited.  I know this isn't always the case; however, I ask anyone to look at this list closely and tell me everyone on it has the resources to kill ragefire without un-interested parties.<br>
<br>
This is not intended to be inflamatory, Please do not find it so.  I am simply voicing what I see as problems.<br>
